Bioluminescence 
The hot weather and calm seas have led to a large growth of bioluminescent plankton at penmon point, during the day it looks like a rusty coloured dirt in the water but come night when disturbed it becomes this beautiful glowing sight.  Unsurprisingly it’s been pretty busy at penmon the last few nights and definitely worth a visit. Swimming with the plankton is one of those unforgettable experiences, just watch out for the jelly fish as well....
